snippet: Fiji’s military ruler for the past eight years appeared to be headed to a decisive victory after the nation voted in a landmark election on Wednesday.
abstract: Fiji's military ruler Commodore Voreqe Bainimarama appears headed to decisive victory in nation's landmark election.
lead_paragraph: Fiji’s military ruler for the past eight years appeared to be headed to a decisive victory after the nation voted in a landmark election on Wednesday.

headline.main: Fiji: Strongman Leading in Election Count
